file: CLAUDE.md
behavior: Project-level instructions for coding agents working in this repo: where to find doctrine/rationale/status docs, mandatory use of the ctx-context/ctx-scan/ctx-verify tools instead of raw cargo or cat, and the lint/secrets policy that governs edits.
edit_notes:
  - Doctrine lives in .context/intent.md and docs/SPEC.md; rationale in docs/DECISIONS.md; current focus in docs/STATUS.md — this file only points at them, do not duplicate their content here.
  - `.context/` is machine-generated by the ctx tools; never hand-edit it.
  - template/ and the root workspace lint configs must be kept in sync; a change to one requires the same change in the other.
functions:
invariants:
  - Reading files must go through native Read/Edit/Grep (or ctx-context for compacted context), never `cat`.
  - `#[allow]` attributes are prohibited anywhere in the codebase.
  - unwrap/expect are permitted only inside `#[test]`/`#[cfg(test)]` bodies; other test helpers must return Result.
  - Functions over 30 lines or files over 250 lines require refactoring first; a one-line `// rationale:` comment is the only accepted exception, and it must be single-line.
  - `.env` (summarizer key) must never be passed to a model or committed.
external_deps:
  - target/debug/ctx-context: generates/reads compacted per-directory or per-file context; must be invoked instead of raw file dumps.
  - target/debug/ctx-scan: reports which `.context/` entries are stale relative to source.
  - target/debug/ctx-verify: single entry point for format/build/lint/test checks; success is `{"status":"pass"}`; direct `cargo` invocation is discouraged.